Visitors view the exhibition Photo: Courtesy of Yang LeiA new exhibition at the Taoxichuan Art Museum in Jingdezhen, East China's Jiangxi Province, is featuring creations from young artists at the Central Academy of Fine Arts (CAFA).According to Zhang Lujiang, the exhibition's curator and also a professor at CAFA, the Works Album of The CAFA NEW Era Thematic Creation Class exhibition uses oil paintings to "represent the vigorous development of well-off life and rural revitalization."The young artists spent weeks in Jingdezhen, known as the capital of ceramics in China, as a part of a residence project to seek inspirations amid the social development and changes in the city. Participating artists include Bai Xiaogang, Li Tianyuan and Qiao Shuyan.